<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14082">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Dentistry.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12983">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Using X-ray (radiographic) films or images and with your counselor's
      guidance, do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12983 mb-requirement-id-12984">
        (a) Study the tooth structure and look for decay. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/09dBTs5ObSU" target="_blank"
          >X-Rays for Cavities (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12983 mb-requirement-id-12985">
        (b) Draw a lower molar, using the radiographs as a guide. Label its
        parts and surfaces. Show surrounding structures such as bone and gum
        tissues.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12983 mb-requirement-id-12986">
        (c) Show on your drawing where the nerves and blood vessels enter and
        leave the tooth.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12983 mb-requirement-id-13026">
        (d) Show on your drawing where bacterial plaque is most likely to be
        found.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12987">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12987 mb-requirement-id-12988">
        (a) Tell or write about what causes dental decay and gum disease.Tell
        how each of the following contributes to dental decay and gum disease:
        bacterial plaque, sugars, and acid. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zGoBFU1q4g0" target="_blank"
          >What Causes Cavities? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BE_h4bTdcdQ" target="_blank"
          >What Causes Tooth Decay? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12987 mb-requirement-id-12989">
        (b) Tell the possible causes for traumatic tooth loss, describe the
        types of mouth guards used to help prevent tooth trauma, and list the
        athletic activities during which a person should wear a mouth guard.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.colgate.com/en-us/oral-health/dental-emergencies-and-sports-safety/three-kinds-of-tooth-injury-that-occur-in-sports"
          target="_blank"
          >The Three Most Common Dental Injuries in Sports and How To Prevent
          Them (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/d0ktAyLnGTE" target="_blank"
          >Why Is Having a Mouthguard Important? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://alignerco.com/blogs/blog/which-sports-require-mouthguards"
          target="_blank"
          >Which Sports Require Mouth Guards? (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12987 mb-requirement-id-12990">
        (c) Explain the first-aid procedure for saving a tooth that has been
        knocked out. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KhHyIeionv8" target="_blank"
          >Knocked Out Teeth | First Aid (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12987 mb-requirement-id-12991">
        (d) Discuss how the use of tobacco products can negatively affect your
        oral health. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/It6DgyGNa48" target="_blank"
          >What Does Smoking Do To Your Teeth? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CAgoECkR354" target="_blank"
          >Vaping &amp; Your Teeth—The Hidden Damage You Need to Know!
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12992">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Arrange for a visit with a dentist. Before you go, ask whether your visit
      can include a dental examination and a plaque-control demonstration.
      Afterward, ask questions about things you want to know. Then tell your
      counselor what the dentist does during a checkup examination.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12970">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12970 mb-requirement-id-12971">
        (a) Name at least five instruments and five pieces of equipment a
        dentist uses. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/l8v6H9WAcGY" target="_blank"
          >12 Essential Dental Instruments Every Dentist Needs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YTNwRc-Rr2M" target="_blank"
          >Dental Tools Used During a Teeth Cleaning—EXPLAINED! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12970 mb-requirement-id-12972">
        (b) With the help of a dentist, prepare a dental stone cast using a
        vibrator, a mixing bowl, a water measure, a plastic measure, model
        stone, and a spatula. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/HN1vdeA4TGs" target="_blank"
          >Mixing and Pouring Dental Stone (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12970 mb-requirement-id-12973">
        (c) Keep a record of everything you eat for three days. Circle those
        items that may provide the sugars that bacterial plaque needs to make
        acid. List snacks that you should avoid to help maintain the best oral
        health. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.bristol.ac.uk/media-library/sites/dental/patient-leaflets/diet-diary.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Diet Diary (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12974">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12974 mb-requirement-id-12975">
        (a) How fluorides help prevent tooth decay and the ways fluorides can be
        provided to the teeth. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/o9UuXmQH1fo" target="_blank"
          >Fluoride: The Superhero of Cavity Fighting (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12974 mb-requirement-id-12976">
        (b) How the mouth is related to the rest of the body. Topics might
        include chewing, saliva, enzymes, nutrition, and speech. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mTPuAul1Ts4" target="_blank"
          >Digestion in the Mouth (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DKW5h17TmMg" target="_blank"
          >Oral Health Is Not Just About the Mouth (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/K2IJY2N5_sY?feature=share"
          target="_blank"
          >Your Mouth and Your Heart Are More Connected Than You Think
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12977">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12977 mb-requirement-id-12978">
        (a) Make a model tooth out of soap, clay, paper-mache, or wax. Using a
        string and a large hand brush, show your troop or a school class proper
        tooth-brushing and flossing procedures. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/dh2El0Ehy0w" target="_blank"
          >Very Easy Teeth Model Making Using Clay(Play-Doh™) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xm9c5HAUBpY" target="_blank"
          >How To Brush Your Teeth (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/HhdoPXNKNm4" target="_blank"
          >How To Floss Your Teeth (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12977 mb-requirement-id-12979">
        (b) Make a poster on the prevention of dental disease. Show the
        importance of good oral health. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5J89gCDt_rk&amp;t=30" target="_blank"
          >The Perfect Oral Health Care Routine (3 Easy Steps in Order)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12977 mb-requirement-id-12980">
        (c) Collect at least five advertisements for different toothpastes. List
        the claims that each one makes. Tell about the accuracy of the
        advertisements.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12977 mb-requirement-id-12981">
        (d) Write a feature story for your school newspaper on the proper care
        of teeth and gums. Include in your story how the use of tobacco products
        can negatively affect a person's oral health.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12977 mb-requirement-id-12982">
        (e) Make drawings and write about the progress of dental decay. Describe
        the types of dental filling and treatments a dentist can use to repair
        dental decay problems. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BwKlQuofmA4" target="_blank"
          >Tooth Decay Progression | 3D Animation (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12993">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Identify three career opportunities that would use skills and knowledge in
      dentistry. Pick one and research the training, education, certification
      requirements, experience, and expenses associated with entering the field.
      Research the prospects for employment, starting salary, advancement
      opportunities and career goals associated with this career. Discuss what
      you learned with your counselor and whether you might be interested in
      this career. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/9dI8FdZruRc" target="_blank"
        >Dental Hygienist Spotlight | Exploring Dental Careers (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/qnsrkWAUchw" target="_blank"
        >Dental Assistant Spotlight | Exploring Dental Careers (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/CNx0tw4RLn4" target="_blank"
        >Join the Dental Workforce: Becoming a Dental Technician (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/xjSg0OIigI0" target="_blank"
        >Career as a Dentist (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/qC1VjKRAl_8" target="_blank"
        >Careers in Dentistry—Dental Receptionist (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/rB7VRAaxxPQ" target="_blank"
        >Master of Science in Dental Materials (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
